Class CategoryKeyMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • Assignment.CategoryKeyMap
  • public class CategoryKeyMap
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores all the keys and category names used as the starting digit for indexing items and promotional sets in the menu. Can hold a maximum of 62 categories limited by the single alpha-numeric key

      • getKey

        public java.lang.String getKey​(java.lang.String type)
        Converts a full category name to its corresponding shortened key. Returns an empty string if the category isn't found in this CategoryKeyMap.
        Parameters:
        type - A String representing the full category name of the items/promotional sets in the menu.
        Returns:
        A 1-character String representing the Shortened key associated to the category name.

      • getCategory

        public java.lang.String getCategory​(java.lang.String key)
        Converts a shortened key to its corresponding full category name. Returns an empty string if the key isn't found in this CategoryKeyMap.
        Parameters:
        key - A 1-character String representing the shortened key associated to the category name.
        Returns:
        A String representing the full category name for the items/promotional sets in the menu.

      • addCategory

        public void addCategory​(java.lang.String type)
        Appends a new category to the object's library as well as automatically generates a new corresponding key. Prints an error message when there is an attempt to call the method when the maximum number of stored categories has already been reached.
        Parameters:
        type - A String representing the full category name for the items/promotional sets in the menu.
